1951;;Young Wives' Tale;;British;;Henry Cass;;Joan Greenwood, Nigel Patrick, Audrey Hepburn;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Young_Wives%27_Tale;;A housing shortage forces two couples, each with an infant child, to share a house. Their inability to find and retain a reliable nanny exacerbates the problems caused by the crowding, and a pretty young lodger (played by Audrey Hepburn) and Sabina's persistent old beau (Guy Middleton) intensify the romantic tensions.